<p>The panel pattern shows either a header link with an optional background colour or with an image, both always with a description. Panels may be used in asides for additional information or combined together to form a <a href="../panel-grid/index.html">panel grid</a>.</p>

<h3>Rules for panels</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Individual panels must only be used in asides.</li>
	<li>Multiple panels must not be used in asides.</li>
	<li>Individual panels must not be used in the main body of pages.</li>
	<li><a href="../panel-grid/index.html">Panel grid</a> pattern must be used to feature multiple panels on a page.</li>
	<li>Any combination of coloured panels can be used on a <a href="../panel-grid/index.html">panel grid</a>.</li>
	<li>Panels with images must only appear in asides.</li>
	<li>Images in panels must be 360 &times; 240 pixels.</li>
</ul>

